| Cyberbullying Gains Momentum in US                                 |
|   from the water-off-of-a-duck's-back dept.                        |
|   posted by Zonk on Thursday June 28, @15:58 (Privacy)             |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/28/1846236          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]interglossa writes "Findings from the Pew Internet Project are being
reported on the BBC news web site, indicating a [1]rising incidence of
cyberbullying among teenagers in the United States. The study showed a
slightly higher incidence among those visiting social networking sites
such as Facebook and MySpace. Tactics cited include being 'the victim of
an aggressive email, IM or text message' and 'having a rumor spread about
them online'. While the concept of cyberbully has been [2]around in the
US for a while, most coverage of the issue has focused on [3]more extreme
examples abroad. It would seem young people in the US are fully adapting
to the anonymity of online interactions."

