+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Ban On Price Floors Abandoned, Internet Prices May Rise            |
|   from the 96-year-old-precedent dept.                             |
|   posted by kdawson on Thursday June 28, @16:44 (The Courts)       |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/28/1542200          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

paro12 and i_like_spam informed us of a 5-4 decision by the US Supreme
Court which [0]abandons a 96-year-old ban on manufacturers and retailers
setting price floors for products. The Slashdot community [1]discussed
the issue when the case was argued back in March. The ruling means that
anti-competitive complaints based on price-fixing will have to be argued
case-by-case and will be harder to prove. Discounts and discounters in
all venues may be under pressure, with [2]internet sales possibly the
hardest hit. "Importantly, this case points a dagger at the heart of the
most consumer-friendly aspects of the Internet. The Internet has shifted
power to the consumer in two ways. First, it allows consumers to search
for and gather information in a cost-effective, efficient manner. Second,
it provides a low-cost means of retailing, making it easy for discounters
to offer products to the public. This combination squeezes excess profits
and inefficiencies out of product prices. Retail price maintenance seeks
to short circuit this extremely consumer friendly process. By setting
minimum prices, manufacturers can build in excess margins for themselves
and for their favored retailers -- prices that consumers have no choice
but to pay."

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/28/1542200

Links:
    0. http://www.nytimes.com/2007/06/29/business/28cnd-bizcourt.html?ex=1340769600&en=0b4c106d96a846ae&ei=5088&partner=rssnyt&emc=rss
    1. http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/03/26/221217&tid=123
    2. http://www.acsblog.org/guest-bloggers-guest-blogger-supreme-court-preview-resale-price-maintenance.html


