+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| National ID May Have Killed Immigration Bill                       |
|   from the choose-your-battles-carefully dept.                     |
|   posted by Zonk on Thursday June 28, @18:12 (Privacy)             |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/28/2014220     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

News.com reports that the immigration reform bill bouncing around in the
Senate for the last few weeks has finally been defeated. The site
speculates that, perhaps, one of the reasons it was finally defeated was
a measure intended to [0]expand the use of Real ID cards. If passed, the
bill would have effectively turned the Real ID system into a National ID
card. "The American Civil Liberties Union, another longtime foe of Real
ID, said the Real ID requirements were a 'poison pill that derailed this
bill, and any future legislation should be written knowing the American
people won't swallow it.' Another section of the immigration bill would
have given $1.5 billion to state officials to pay for Real ID compliance.
Even if the immigration bill is goes nowhere, however, the Real ID Act is
still in effect. It says, starting on May 11, 2008, Americans will need a
federally-approved ID card to travel on an airplane, open a bank account,
collect Social Security payments or take advantage of nearly any
government service." As we've discussed before, [1]several states have
rebelled against the implementation of Real ID.

Discuss this story at:
    http://politics.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/28/2014220

Links:
    0. http://news.com.com/2100-7348_3-6193916.html?part=rss&tag=2547-1_3-0-20&subj=news
    1. http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/12/148203&tid=158


